  <Section heading="The short version">
    <p>Started freelancing in 2016 — small businesses, brand work, landing pages. In 2021 joined SupportYourApp as a UX/UI designer, first time working inside a real product team.</p>
    <p>In 2023 joined Quidget as the founding designer. Built everything from scratch: brand, dashboard, onboarding, widget, marketing site.</p>
    <p>Since 2025 I've been at Headway, working on conversion and growth for a book summary app with <em>55+ million users.</em></p>
  </Section>

  <Section heading="How I work">
    <p>Before changing anything, I define the exact hypothesis: what am I testing, and how will I know if it worked? If the result doesn't tell me what caused it, the test was poorly designed — not just the outcome, the question itself.</p>
    <p>I work closely with AI throughout — brainstorming, prototyping, gathering context, building. Not as a shortcut, but as a thinking partner that makes the gap between idea and testable thing much smaller.</p>
    <p>I write the copy too. Not as a bonus — because if I can't write the words, I don't yet understand the problem.</p>
  </Section>

  <Section heading="Say hi">
    <p>Based in Kyiv. Outside the work: film photography, PlayStation, and a probably-never-ending apartment decoration project. Always up for coffee or ramen.</p>
